Let me analyze this bug. I need to look at the ToolExecutionComponent and how it handles errors for different tools.

Found the bug. Let me examine the `write` tool case in detail and compare with how `edit` handles errors:

**Root Cause Analysis:**

In `tool-execution.ts`, the `formatToolExecution()` method handles different built-in tools. Looking at the `write` case (lines 430-453):

```typescript
} else if (this.toolName === "write") {
    const rawPath = this.args?.file_path || this.args?.path || "";
    const path = shortenPath(rawPath);
    const fileContent = this.args?.content || "";
    // ... renders fileContent from args ...

    // NO ERROR HANDLING - missing check for this.result?.isError
}
```

Compare this to the `edit` case (lines 455-482) which properly handles errors:

```typescript
} else if (this.toolName === "edit") {
    // ...
    if (this.result?.isError) {
        // Show error from result
        const errorText = this.getTextOutput();
        if (errorText) {
            text += `\n\n${theme.fg("error", errorText)}`;
        }
    } else if (this.result?.details?.diff) {
        // ...
    }
}
```

The `write` tool case:
1. Only renders the content from `args` (what's being written)
2. Never checks `this.result?.isError`
3. Never calls `this.getTextOutput()` to display error messages

Other tools (`bash`, `read`, `ls`, `find`, `grep`) all display output from `this.getTextOutput()` which includes error text. Only `write` is missing this.

**Proposed Fix:**

Add error handling to the `write` case in `formatToolExecution()`:

```typescript
} else if (this.toolName === "write") {
    const rawPath = this.args?.file_path || this.args?.path || "";
    const path = shortenPath(rawPath);
    const fileContent = this.args?.content || "";
    // ... existing code to render header and content ...

    // ADD: Show error if tool execution failed
    if (this.result?.isError) {
        const errorText = this.getTextOutput();
        if (errorText) {
            text += `\n\n${theme.fg("error", errorText)}`;
        }
    }
}
```

**Affected File:**
- `packages/coding-agent/src/modes/interactive/components/tool-execution.ts` (lines ~430-453)

Now let me update the changelog:

Fixed. Summary:

**Change:** Added error handling to the `write` tool case in `ToolExecutionComponent.formatToolExecution()`

**File:** `packages/coding-agent/src/modes/interactive/components/tool-execution.ts`

The `write` tool was only rendering the content from args, never checking `this.result?.isError` or displaying error text. Added the same error handling pattern used by the `edit` tool:

```typescript
// Show error if tool execution failed
if (this.result?.isError) {
    const errorText = this.getTextOutput();
    if (errorText) {
        text += `\n\n${theme.fg("error", errorText)}`;
    }
}
```

